RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WISE VERDICT saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far bend and kicked clear in the lane. WILLY THE COBBLER raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and gained ground late. ROCKIN THE DAD BOD raced in the two path early, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, swung out to the four path coming around the second turn and kept on in the lane. SURPRSINGLYPERFECT saved ground around the first bend, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and gained ground mildly late. FURY KAP raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn and faded in the stretch. FLATOUT WINNER saved ground early, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path, took a bad step while gaining ground in the final furlong, stumbled and lost his rider and was vanned off. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE INCIDENT IN THE STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 7 1/2F Turf CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 25 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIKE FINE WINE saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and dueled to the wire to get up late. RED SUNSHINE led the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path, was headed in upper stretch and battled back gamely in the final furlong to narrowly miss. DR Z'S ELSA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the four path and improved position in the stretch. MARK OF VICTORY raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the second bend and gained ground late. ROLL GYPSY ROLL raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, moved up from the three path coming around the far turn and flattened out in the lane. SMART LEAH raced in the two path around the first bend, tracked the pace setter up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and faded in the lane. GRACEFUL MOON saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back to trail the field from the rail around the far turn and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAT'S GAL brushed with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the way on the inside up the backstretch, drew off racing in the two path around the turn and in upper stretch and held a dwindling lead to the wire. MIZ MCCOY raced off the pace on the outside early, came around the turn in the two path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. DIXIE GIRL TO raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and finished evenly. TAMMY MACHO bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and showed no kick. NONA bumped and was forced back by the horses to both sides leaving the gate, moved up to chase the leader up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: Pleasant Hills Training Center Brewer Paul and Brewer Denise

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 97. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 29 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred C laiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 25 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KING OF THE KIDS saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and gained ground late to get up for the win in time. MACEDONIAN RULER (AUS) raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, navigated the far bend from the three path and gained ground on the outside late to narrowly miss. THIRTY SECONDS OUT saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and was caught near the wire. MOVE OVER (GB) raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and kept on to the finish. BRIX bobbled slightly leaving the gate, saved ground around the first bend, chased the leader up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. SKIPPY'S STRIKE raced in the two path early, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn, and flattened out in the final furlong. OF GOOD REPORT saved ground around the first bend, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAYHAYCAPTAIN JAC led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and kicked clear in the stretch. EYE ON RY tracked the leader from the middle of the pack through the opening quarter mile, saved ground around the far turn and improved position on the rail late. R VOO'S TABOO chased the leader early, came around the turn in the three path and kept on to the finish. B L'S CONCERTO raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and flattened out in the stretch. WHODOESITBETTER trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and showed no kick. SWEET ANALYZER raced off the pace on the inside through the early going, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 5F Turf CR: 73. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 25 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHISTLER was reluctant to load, broke well and chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path and edged clear late. STABILITY dueled between horses early, continued to battle from the two path around the bend, was caught in midstretch and kept on from there. JACKSON ACTION stalked the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position mildly in the stretch. HARLEEZY tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and chased on to the finish. ANGEL OF ATTACK raced off the pace early, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. PRINCE OF EARL trailed far behind field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and was empty in the lane. VICTORYFORTHEPOSSE dueled on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 99. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Th ree Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RECKONING DAY tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and edged up for the win late. EUROMANTIC led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path coming around the turn, dug in in the stretch and was caught late. INTER MIAMI raced off the pace on the outside early, came around the turn in the three path and improved position in the lane. GRAY MAGICIAN raced off the pace on the inside through the opening quarter, navigated the bend from the three path and made up some ground in the stretch. CITRUS BAY chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and tired further in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Reckoning Day
ENTRY.OWNER: Woolley Jr Bennie L and Herwig Steve

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 29500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR HOME STATE BRED ALLOWANCE SINCE MAY 26 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. T hree Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOLLY'S ANGEL raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and kicked clear in the lane. CLUBHOUSE SAINT raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and gained ground late. IT'S HER TIME saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, was caught in midstretch and kept on to the wire. ELUSIVE AMELIA chased the leader from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn still in the two path and finished evenly. SEA LEVEL raced in the three path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the far turn in the two path and showed no kick. TOM'S GIRL saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the two path and made no bid. COUNTESS OF CAIRO trailed the field the entire way around the oval, raced in the two and three path throughout and was not a factor.
